Package: eden
Type: Package
Title: eDNA Depth-invariant Encoder Normalization
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Sk Injamamul", "Islam", email = "you@upei.ca",
                  role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: A deep generative normalization framework for environmental DNA
    (eDNA) metabarcoding count data. EDEN uses a variational autoencoder with
    a zero-inflated negative binomial likelihood to learn a depth-invariant
    latent representation of community composition, using all sequencing reads
    rather than discarding data through rarefaction. An optional phylogenetic
    extension (EDEN-P) applies phylogenetic kernel smoothing to per-taxon
    dispersion estimates, gated by a Pagel's lambda test for phylogenetic
    signal. The package returns both a reconstructed-count phyloseq object
    (a drop-in replacement for rarefied data, compatible with all downstream
    beta-diversity methods) and the depth-invariant latent embedding with
    per-sample uncertainty, letting the user choose the representation
    appropriate to their analysis.
